translation.en: [in alien language] Attack!
Ah oui, I would like to purchase cryptocurrency -that was started by a famous DJ. -[humans screaming]
translation.es: Oui, quisiera comprar la criptomoneda creada por un famoso DJ.

translation.en: Quoi?
[in French] I wasted my life.
[in English] Europe has fallen. Washington, D.C. is all that's left.
translation.es: Europa ha caído. Solo queda Washington D. C.

translation.en: It's been… a pleasure serving with all of you.
translation.es: Ha sido un placer servir a la Patria con ustedes,

translation.en: Except Randall.
My dad's your boss.
-Not no more, champ. -[woman shrieks]
Who's them?
-[heroic music playing] -[man grunts]
-Lucy, look out! -[Lucy yelps]
You know, three days ago, if somebody told me aliens were gonna blow up the planet,
translation.es: Si me hubieran dicho que los alienígenas destruirían el planeta,

translation.en: but I'd get to meet you…
translation.es: pero que te conocería a ti…

translation.en: Oh, okay. Now?
Uh, uh, kind of a weird time, but--
translation.es: No es un buen momento, pero…

translation.en: Go save the planet, Matty!
I got this.
I may not be smart.
The only real job I ever had
was letting scientists spray perfume in my eyes.
translation.es: fue que unos científicos me rociaran los ojos con perfume.

translation.en: So, yeah, I may not be good at lists,
translation.es: No seré bueno para hacer listas

translation.en: or, like, planning how I'm gonna get home from places--
translation.es: ni para hallar el camino de vuelta a casa…

translation.en: Okay, cool! Earth is counting on you.
translation.es: Bueno, genial. La Tierra depende de ti.

translation.en: But if there's one thing I can do, it's bring the high heat.
translation.es: Pero lo que sí sé hacer es lanzar una bola rápida.

translation.en: [in alien language] I wasted my life!
[in English] Yes!
-Matty! -[Matty grunts]
Hang on!
Well, butter my biscuits.
That boy did it. He destroyed the alien hive mind.
translation.es: El muchacho logró destruir la mente colmena alienígena.

translation.en: Now that's what I call a home run.
translation.es: Eso es lo que llamo un jonrón.

translation.en: [Lucy] Oh, now what do we do?
Now we rebuild, or whatever.
translation.es: Reconstruiremos todo o algo por el estilo.

translation.en: Okay, so now I'm just fully naked.
And that's the guy who defeated me? Cool.
translation.es: ¿Ese es el que me derrotó? Genial.

translation.en: I totally blew up that ship.
translation.es: Hice volar esa nave en pedazos.

translation.en: [imitating Borat] Very nice! My wife!
I don't think I caught your name earlier, young man.
Senator Cartwright LaMarr.
And it is an honor.
Thanks to you, a small, precious piece of humanity survived.
translation.es: Gracias a usted, sobrevivió una pequeña parte de la humanidad.

translation.en: But these people are gonna need someone to lead them.
A new hero for a new world.
translation.es: Un nuevo héroe para un nuevo mundo.

translation.en: President Mulligan?
-[all cheering] -I like the sound of that, Senator.
And of course, you'll need someone experienced to be your number two.
translation.es: Claro, necesitará alguien experimentado que sea su número dos.

translation.en: [chuckles] Number two.
But yeah, sure. Welcome aboard, chief.
translation.es: Sí, claro. Bienvenido a bordo, jefe.

translation.en: And I know exactly who I want to be my First Lady.
translation.es: Sé a quién quiero de primera dama.

translation.en: [Lucy] The grenade pin!
It's like a fairy tale
'cause we just met, and before that, I was unconscious for a while.
translation.es: porque acabamos de conocernos y, antes, estuve inconsciente.

translation.en: [all cheering] Matty and Lucy! Matty and Lucy!
Don't worry, me and Lucy are gonna fix everything.
translation.es: Descuiden. Lucy y yo arreglaremos todo.

translation.en: The end.
[all continue cheering] Matty and Lucy! Matty and Lucy!
I should've stayed awake in school more.
translation.es: No debí haberme dormido en clase.

translation.en: Matty-- Uh, Mr. President.
Is inflammable the same as flammable or the opposite?
Okay, it's the same.
English is funny, right?
[Lucy] Oh, so sad.
[Matty] Oh, I know.
All that air and space just… [scoffs] …gone.
God, this has gotta be the worst time ever to be president.
translation.es: Me tocó el peor momento para ser presidente.

translation.en: We don't even have electricity.
It's warm! Why?
For, like, the hospitals or… or whatever.
Well, at least we still have each other
translation.es: Al menos, nos tenemos a nosotros.

translation.en: and that silly Washington Wizards mascot to make us laugh.
translation.es: Y a la mascota de los Washington Wizards para divertirnos.

translation.en: [mascot, muffled] Oh God! The costume is fused to my skin!
translation.es: ¡El disfraz se me pegó a la piel!

translation.en: I love that guy.
Well said, madam.
We are indeed fortunate to have such an eloquent and exotic First Lady.
translation.es: Tenemos suerte de contar con una primera dama exótica y elocuente.

translation.en: Well, I'm not First Lady yet, but I'm looking forward to it.
translation.es: No soy primera dama, pero ya quiero serlo.

translation.en: As Miss Nevada, I started a program that matched old magic-show tigers with prisoners.
translation.es: Como Miss Nevada, me dediqué a juntar tigres de shows de magia con prisioneros.

translation.en: Just think what I could do as First Lady.
translation.es: Imaginen lo que haría si lo fuera.

translation.en: Oh my God, it's Matty and Lucy!
Well, it is indeed.
Matty and Lucy! [all chanting] Matty and Lucy! Matty and Lucy! Matty and Lucy!
-[Matty] Ah, you know it! Stay in school. -[Lucy] Ah, mwah!
[all continue] Matty and Lucy!
Ugh, phones.
-Remember not answering phones? -Aw! I miss that.
translation.es: ¿Recuerdas cuando no los atendíamos? Extraño eso.

translation.en: So, where you from?
Oh, right. Reno. You? Boston. Go all the sports.
translation.es: - Sí, claro, de Reno. ¿Y tú? - Boston. Fan de todos los deportes.

translation.en: So, uh, first time in D.C.?
First time anywhere.
What else? What kind of Catholic are you?
Look, I really do wanna get to know you,
but I think there's more important stuff for us to do first.
translation.es: pero hay cosas más importantes que hacer.

translation.en: Oh yeah, totally. Say no more.
translation.es: Sí, claro. No se diga más.

translation.en: Man.
Ah, jeez.
Come on, Matty, I believe in you.
You… you do? You blew up an entire alien army.
You can totally figure out how to "restart Fast & Furious franchise."
translation.es: Puedes ingeniártelas para relanzar la franquicia de Rápido y furioso.

translation.en: Or one of the other ones.
It's not like you have to do everything alone.
translation.es: No tienes por qué hacer todo solo.

translation.en: You've got me. And LaMarr.
translation.es: Nos tienes a mí y a LaMarr.

translation.en: Yeah, where'd that dude go?
All in favor? All opposed? Zero-zero again.
translation.es: ¿Todos a favor? ¿En contra? Empate otra vez.

translation.en: That means the vice president breaks the tie,
and I vote "aye."
Money is now considered a person under the law.
translation.es: Por ley, el dinero se considerará persona.

translation.en: Moving on.
I'm just saying, I bet there's lots of people that can help out.
translation.es: Digo que hay mucha gente que puede ayudar.

translation.en: Mr. LaMarr is already doing politics.
translation.es: El Sr. LaMarr ya hace política.

translation.en: Why don't we get, like, experts to do the other stuff?
translation.es: ¿Por qué no buscamos expertos para lo demás?

translation.en: Lucy, dude, that's a great idea!
Yes. That way, I can focus on the stuff I'm good at,
translation.es: Así podré concentrarme en lo que sé hacer mejor,

translation.en: like giving everyone cool nicknames, L-Dog,
translation.es: como ponerles a todos buenos apodos. "Luciérnaga".

translation.en: while the experts take care of, you know, water and food and all that stuff.
translation.es: Los expertos se ocuparán del agua, la comida y todo eso.

translation.en: And hopefully figure out why the birds are acting so horny.
translation.es: Y de averiguar por qué las aves están tan cachondas.

translation.en: Well, what a wonderful idea it was to assemble this here cabinet, Miss Suwan.
translation.es: Qué gran idea tuvo de armar este gabinete, Srta. Suwan.

translation.en: I do so enjoy when beauty queens dictate executive branch policy.
translation.es: Me gusta que las reinas de belleza formulen políticas del poder ejecutivo.

translation.en: And you are very welcome.
Okay, so these are, like, the smartest people on Earth.
translation.es: Estas son las personas más listas de la Tierra.

translation.en: Yes. Well, during the attack, most of our nation's scientists and intellectuals
translation.es: Bueno, durante el ataque, casi todos los científicos e intelectuales

translation.en: fled the planet on Jeff Bezos' space ark.
translation.es: dejaron el planeta en el arca espacial de Bezos.

translation.en: [Bezos] Everyone laughed at Bezos, but who's laughing now?
translation.es: Todos se reían de Bezos. ¿A ver quién se ríe ahora?

translation.en: Bezos is! [chuckles]
Bezos wins--
But that's why you've got me to handle all the boring old legislating.
translation.es: Para la aburrida acción de legislar, estoy yo.

translation.en: I've been Chair of the Senate Subcommittee on Loopholes and Minutiae
translation.es: Presidí el subcomité del Senado sobre Vacíos Legales y Minucias

translation.en: since I was knee-high to a crumbleberry.
No, totally. You're my main guy. But, I mean, we could use some help.
translation.es: Sí, claro. Eres mi mano derecha, pero vendría bien algo de ayuda.

translation.en: Starting with Dr. Farrah Braun. She's a female scientist.
translation.es: Comenzando por la Dra. Farrah Braun, una mujer científica.

translation.en: Just scientist is fine.
I was at DARPA.
Right now, my focus is on getting the tap water to stop doing this.
translation.es: Ahora, mi objetivo es conseguir que el agua del grifo no haga esto.

translation.en: -Oh God. -[LaMarr groans]
But I kind of have my hands full with the boys.
translation.es: Pero estoy ocupada con los niños.

translation.en: -Mom, Yu-Gi-Oh! won't play! -I wanna watch Yu-Gi-Oh!
translation.es: - Mamá, Yu-Gi-Oh! no funciona. - ¡Quiero ver Yu-Gi-Oh!

translation.en: We've been over this, the Internet doesn't exist anymore.
translation.es: Les dije que internet no existe más.

translation.en: There's no screens. [chuckles]
My nanny melted, and now there's no screens!
translation.es: Mi niñera se derritió, y no hay más pantallas.

translation.en: If there's no electricity, is there no electronica?
translation.es: Si no hay electricidad, ¿no hay música electrónica?

translation.en: Isn't that what the "elec" stands for? What will the clubs in Ibiza play?
translation.es: ¿"Elec" no significa eso? ¿Qué pasarán en las discos de Ibiza?

translation.en: We Found Jeremy here at the British Embassy.
translation.es: Jeremy estaba en la embajada británica.

translation.en: Listen to that accent. Guy's a genius.
translation.es: Escucha ese acento. Es un genio.

translation.en: Are we to take Molly and listen to silence?
translation.es: ¿Cómo tomaremos éxtasis y escucharemos el silencio?

translation.en: Maybe Professor Prioleau can answer that. He does history.
translation.es: Preguntémosle a Prioleau, el profesor de Historia.

translation.en: Oh, but that wasn't a history question. And it was rhetorical.
translation.es: No fue una pregunta de historia, sino retórica.

translation.en: Well, we're going around the table in order, so--
Yep, okay. Hi. I'm Simon Prioleau.
translation.es: Está bien. Hola. Soy Simon Prioleau.

translation.en: I'm a Georgetown post-doc with a focus on 19th-century fonts--
translation.es: Soy investigador y me dedico a las tipografías del…

translation.en: Okay, cool. Now all of you are gonna love this next guy.
translation.es: Sí, genial. A todos les encantará el próximo.

translation.en: General Scarpaccio, sir.
Yeah, um, so as an important army man, do I get to, like, shoot guns and stuff?
translation.es: Sí, como hombre del ejército, ¿puedo disparar armas y esas cosas?

translation.en: Of course, sir. Thank you for your service.
translation.es: Claro, señor. Gracias por su servicio.

translation.en: I'm sorry, how old is he?
Whoa, dude. One, racist.
Two, support the troops. [whispers] Sorry.
translation.es: Dos, apoye a las tropas. Perdón.

translation.en: We also found a dentist and a carpenter.
translation.es: Encontramos una odontóloga y una carpintera.

translation.en: No, I sang backup vocals for The Carpenters.
translation.es: No, cantaba en el coro los Carpenters.

translation.en: And a guy who owns a shoe store that didn't get blown up.
translation.es: Y el dueño de la zapatería que sigue en pie.

translation.en: Lots of debris out there! [chuckles] Folks are gonna need shoes more than ever!
translation.es: Hay muchos escombros. Se necesitarán muchos zapatos.

translation.en: And as future First Lady and your Miss America,
translation.es: Y como futura primera dama y su Miss EE. UU.,

translation.en: my causes are animals, childhood obesity, and elder literacy.
translation.es: me dedico a la obesidad infantil, a los animales y a alfabetizar ancianos.

translation.en: Lucy Suwan, Washoe County, 5'6".
translation.es: Lucy Suwan, condado de Washoe, 1.67 m.

translation.en: Wait, but if there's no food, then there's no obesity, right?
translation.es: Claro, pero si no hay comida, no hay obesidad, ¿cierto?

translation.en: You solved it!
[gasps] Yeah. And I haven't seen many old people since the attack.
translation.es: Sí, y no vi muchos ancianos luego del ataque.

translation.en: We think the aliens targeted them first because they assumed that we revered our elders.
translation.es: Los alienígenas los atacaron primero porque creían que los venerábamos.

translation.en: But I am worried about the animals.
I did a fact-finding tour of the National Zoo this morning,
translation.es: Hice un recorrido de reconocimiento del zoológico,

translation.en: and the facts I found were not good facts.
We'd already be out of food if the elephant hadn't 'sploded. [Lucy gasps] Oh.
translation.es: No tendríamos comida si el elefante no hubiera estallado.

translation.en: But the biggest issue's power.
The backup generator barely produces enough juice for the freezer and my Foreman Grill.
translation.es: El generador no produce energía para la nevera y la parrilla eléctrica.

translation.en: Are you sure I can't get you any elephant?
No, thanks.
[muttering] Elephant was my friend.
[screeching] I DON'T SPEAK GORILLA!!!
[in English] So the zoo has a generator?
Those poor animals might be the last of their kind left on Earth.
translation.es: Deben ser los últimos animales que quedan en la Tierra.

translation.en: We can't let them die out.
Speaking of losing things forever, eh,
the Smithsonian is kinda still on fire.
Imagine if we lost Woodrow Wilson's Klan hood.
translation.es: Imaginen si perdiéramos su capucha del KKK de Woodrow Wilson.

translation.en: Why was that my example?
Okay, sure, but the bottled water is running out fast.
translation.es: Bien, pero el agua embotellada se acaba.

translation.en: ♪ And the people need music ♪
-♪ Whoo! ♪ -So where do we start, sir?
Um, why is everybody looking at me? I… I don't know. You're the experts.
translation.es: ¿Por qué me miran? No sé. Ustedes son los expertos.

translation.en: Yes, but you're the president because you're good at throwing.
translation.es: Sí, pero usted es el presidente porque hace buenos lanzamientos.

translation.en: LaMarr, what are the things that you're always having me sign?
translation.es: LaMarr, ¿qué es eso que me haces firmar siempre?

translation.en: Ah! Executive order.
You guys do it.
The president's right.
All this silly-billyness is beneath him.
translation.es: Él no está para estas tonterías.

translation.en: Sir, your job isn't to sit in boring meetings and make boring decisions.
translation.es: No debe estar en reuniones aburridas tomando decisiones tediosas.

translation.en: You and Lucy, y'all's job is to give people hope.
translation.es: Su misión y la de Lucy es darle esperanzas a la gente.

translation.en: Those folks need something to rally behind.
translation.es: Esa gente necesita algo que apoyar.

translation.en: They need their heroes to distract them from, uh--
translation.es: Necesitan héroes que los distraigan de…

translation.en: Oh my word.
Have we even had a victory parade for y'all yet?
translation.es: ¿No hemos hecho un desfile de la victoria?

translation.en: No, we haven't!
What the hell?
Do I get to wave?
-[triumphant music playing] -[crowd clamoring, cheering]
-Hi there. How's it going? -Thank you.
-You're welcome, for everything. -Thank you.
I actually like this. Pulling a vehicle is an honor in my culture.
translation.es: Me gusta. En mi cultura, es un honor tirar de un coche.

translation.en: No one believes you, pal.
I was a general. They named a kind of hat after me.
translation.es: Era general. Le pusieron mi nombre a un sombrero.

translation.en: Well, not bad, huh, Luce?
Everyone seems happy.
It's like a Reno car dealership opening, and we're Frank Sinatra Jr.
translation.es: Es como inaugurar una licorería y ser alcohólico.

translation.en: To us.
How is this cold? Where did you get a generator?
translation.es: ¿Por qué está fría? ¿De dónde sacaste un generador?

translation.en: Oh, um, the generator store. Yeah, nah, it's still open.
translation.es: De la tienda de generadores. Aún está abierta.

translation.en: [zookeeper] I'm sorry, Kojo.
Some idiot stole the generator, and all the food spoiled.
translation.es: Un idiota robó el generador. Se pudrió la comida.

translation.en: You and the others will need to fend for yourselves from now on.
translation.es: Tú y los demás deberán arreglárselas solos.

translation.en: [muttering] Geri friend. Geri spared in new world Kojo build.
translation.es: Geri, amiga. Tener lugar en el nuevo mundo de Kojo.

translation.en: And… and who's to say what cold even means?
Right? I mean, like, what's cold to me
translation.es: Lo que es frío para mí

translation.en: might feel burning hot to, like, an ice person.
translation.es: puede ser caliente para el que vive en el hielo.

translation.en: -[woman screams] -[Matty] Oh my God!
[Lucy gasps] Matty!
Unrelated!
This is all his fault.
Dude, shut up!
-[booing] -[man] How could you?
-[woman] You're the animal! -[man] You're the worst!
-[booing continues] -[scoffs] What's their problem?
So a bunch of zoo animals escaped.
It was only 'cause I wanted to give everyone free beer.
translation.es: Solo quería regalar cerveza a todos.

translation.en: Uh, yes, splendid.
translation.es: Magnífico, pero su público es cambiante.

translation.en: But your loving public can be fickle, so we need to pivot,
translation.es: Magnífico, pero su público es cambiante. Debemos dar un giro como Stonewall Jackson en la Guerra Civil

translation.en: like Stonewall Jackson at Chancellorsville,
translation.es: Debemos dar un giro como Stonewall Jackson en la Guerra Civil

translation.en: or Dr. Martin Luther King also.
Is this really going to distract us?
I mean, we're running out of medicine and dinosaur chicken nuggets.
translation.es: Casi no tenemos medicinas ni nuggets con forma de dinosaurio.

translation.en: And no, my boys won't eat regular chicken nuggets.
translation.es: Mis hijos no comen de los comunes.

translation.en: Have you tried telling them that they're actually dinosaur eggs?
translation.es: ¿No probó con decirles que son huevos de dinosaurio?

translation.en: Of course I have, Mr. Vice President. I have two PhDs.
translation.es: Por supuesto, señor. Hice dos doctorados.

translation.en: Oh, this will all just blow over.
Remember when Prince Charles dressed that servant girl up like the queen
translation.es: Una vez, el príncipe Carlos vistió de reina a una criada

translation.en: and tried to drown her in the bath?
translation.es: e intentó ahogarla en la tina.

translation.en: That was only in the news for like a day.
Oh my God, princes aren't real, man. This is real life.
translation.es: Pero los príncipes no existen. Esto es la vida real.

translation.en: And I'm afraid the news cycle isn't as fast as it used to be.
translation.es: Creo que las noticias ya no corren como antes.

translation.en: Hey, everybody!
The president took the generator, and now all the zoo animals got away.
translation.es: El presidente robó el generador, y los animales huyeron del zoo.

translation.en: Did you see? There's animals everywhere 'cause of the president!
translation.es: Hay animales sueltos por culpa del presidente.

translation.en: Well, I agree with the protesters.
So boo! Boo to you!
translation.es: Así que yo también te abucheo.

translation.en: You knew animals was one of my causes.
translation.es: Sabías que los animales eran mi causa.

translation.en: Okay, executive order! Everyone's gotta be nice to me again.
translation.es: ¡Decreto presidencial! Todos volverán a ser buenos conmigo.

translation.en: Listen, we need some good news.
Something to distract our slack-jawed constituents.
translation.es: Algo que distraiga a los embrutecidos votantes.

translation.en: I'm having a sale on Reeboks.
I might be able to reverse-engineer some of my military tech to purify the water,
translation.es: Podría simplificar la tecnología militar para purificar el agua,

translation.en: but I don't have childcare in the afternoon.
translation.es: pero no tengo niñera por la tarde.

translation.en: Uh-huh. And who's taking care of your children now?
Uh, TOD-209 has them.
TOD is a, uh, cyborg super soldier my lab was working on.
translation.es: Es el supersoldado cíborg construido por mi laboratorio.

translation.en: He helped fight the aliens.
No! No, bad TOD! Fight the aliens!
I told them he wasn't ready.
translation.es: Les dije que no estaba listo.

translation.en: I'm sorry, that's who's watching your kids?
You really need to choose between your career and family, Doctor.
translation.es: Debe elegir entre su familia y su carrera, doctora.

translation.en: Still?
Uh, um, well, maybe saving the artifacts in the old Smithsonian--
translation.es: Quizá si guardamos los objetos en el viejo Smithsoniano…

translation.en: "President bad."
Check the other side, General. Does it say "mama jama"?
translation.es: Lea del otro lado. ¿No dice que es una broma?

translation.en: It's just one side.
We gotta nip this unrest in its bud, sir, which means doing something big.
translation.es: Debemos aplacar el malestar. Hay que hacer algo importante.

translation.en: You and Miss Suwan are getting married tomorrow.
translation.es: Mañana se casará con la Srta. Suwan.

translation.en: Tomorrow?
A big ol' royal wedding will change the conversation,
translation.es: Una boda real los hará cambiar de tema,

translation.en: give the people something to get excited about.
translation.es: le dará a la gente algo de entusiasmo.

translation.en: Hey, for our first dance, you can pick anything from Jock Jams.
translation.es: Para el primer baile, elige algo de los 80.

translation.en: -I… I… I don't wanna marry you. -Huh?
I thought I could do this, but those animals don't have homes now
translation.es: Creí que podría, pero esos animales están desamparados por tu culpa.

translation.en: because of you!
translation.es: pero esos animales están desamparados por tu culpa.

translation.en: Who cares?
People deserve a generator, not animals.
translation.es: La gente necesita el generador, no los animales.

translation.en: It goes God, Jesus, people, animals,
translation.es: El orden es Dios, Jesús, la gente, los animales,

translation.en: plants, fish, bugs, dirt--
translation.es: las plantas, los peces, los bichos…

translation.en: We can circle back to the nuptials.
translation.es: Más tarde hablaremos de la boda.

translation.en: Uh, what else distracts ordinary folks?
translation.es: ¿Qué otra cosa distrae a la gente?

translation.en: Uh, does anyone have a trampoline?
-Knock, knock. -Simon.
Um, I would've called first, but, uh, there are no phones.
translation.es: Habría llamado, pero no hay teléfonos.

translation.en: -In my head, I thought that was a joke. -Really? How so?
translation.es: - A mí me pareció gracioso. - ¿Ah, sí? ¿Por qué?

translation.en: Anyhoozzle, I just thought, 'Hey, you know, Dr. Braun's a scientist."
translation.es: En fin, pensé: "Bueno, la Dra. Braun es científica.

translation.en: "Maybe she has some science stuff that could put out all those museum fires."
translation.es: Quizá tenga algo para apagar el fuego de los museos".

translation.en: Well, last year, I was working on a cloud-seeding program for DoD.
translation.es: El año pasado, trabajé en siembra de nubes para Defensa.

translation.en: The idea was if we could make it rain,
Kim-Jong Un would have to cancel all his picnics.
translation.es: a Kim-Jong Un se le arruinarían los pícnics.

translation.en: But now I can't access the DARPA Intranet,
translation.es: Pero, como no puedo ingresar en la intranet,

translation.en: so I have to go through the paper files, which are a mess.
translation.es: debo revisar los papeles, y son un desastre.

translation.en: This isn't even in the right box.
Ugh, boxes, am I right? [groans]
translation.es: Cajas. Qué fastidio. CONTROL MENTAL 5 G

translation.en: What's that? Sorry, I'm a little fried.
Work, and since the invasion, I'm all my kids have.
translation.es: Trabajo, y ahora mis hijos solo me tienen a mí.

translation.en: [boy whimpers] Giant bugs.
No, don't bomb GameStop!
-[Simon] Ugh. -It's overwhelming.
We may be the two smartest people left on Earth, Simon,
translation.es: Debemos ser los únicos dos inteligentes.

translation.en: but are we supposed to save civilization all by ourselves?
[TOD-209] TOD get it. Is stressful time.
-Sounds like we all need unwind. -[Simon gasps]
Well…
-Hmm? -[Simon] Mmm!
[scoffs] First you blow up my planet, now you block my bowling alley?
translation.es: ¿Primero destruyes mi planeta y ahora bloqueas mi bolera?

translation.en: If you let me go, you can bowl all you want.
translation.es: Déjame ir y jugarás todo lo que quieras.

translation.en: And it's not even candlepin.
translation.es: Encima, es la única variante que hay.

translation.en: Well, no wonder everybody hates Nixon.
translation.es: Con razón todos odian a Nixon.

translation.en: Ugh! What else can go wrong today?
Axatrax, two days ago, I was a hero,
translation.es: Axatrax, hace dos días, era un héroe,

translation.en: president, engaged to a pre-attack 11,
translation.es: un presidente comprometido con una bomba despampanante,

translation.en: and now everyone's pissed at me.
Look… [sighs] …I get it.
I was in command of an unstoppable army,
I had the kitchen of my dreams, and now--
translation.es: tenía la cocina de mis sueños, y ahora…

translation.en: You're a loser. Everyone hates you.
translation.es: Eres un fracasado, y todos te odian.

translation.en: I hear you, bro.
Oh, wonderful, we're bonding.
Do you have sarcasm here?
I don't know what your life was like before you totally beefed your invasion,
translation.es: No sé cómo era tu vida antes de que cagaras tu invasión,

translation.en: but all I've ever done is screw up.
translation.es: pero yo siempre metí la pata.

translation.en: My scholarship, my baseball career, the hockey league I started with dogs,
translation.es: Mi beca, mi carrera en el béisbol, la liga de hockey que creé para perros.

translation.en: but then I whipped a grenade into that vent--
translation.es: Luego, arrojé una granada al respiradero…

translation.en: I told them I wanted vent covers. What was the point of all those meetings?
translation.es: Les dije que los taparan. ¿Para qué tantas reuniones?

translation.en: I finally got a win.
I mean, saving the planet is, like, the first thing I've ever done right.
translation.es: Salvar el planeta es lo primero que me salió bien.

translation.en: Why can't every day be like that?
Oh, so you want us to invade again?
No, but--
-Huh. -What?
What?
Everyone watch out! It escaped!
I did not escape! This man let me out--
translation.es: No me escapé. Me dejó salir…

translation.en: -Ow, stop that! -[Matty grunts]
Oh come on! Ow!
-Get off my plane! -[Axatrax continues grunting]
Lucy, look! I'm saving you from the aliens again!
translation.es: ¡Mira, Lucy! ¡Volví a salvarte de los alienígenas!

translation.en: Come on, let's make out!
This is pathetic.
You let him out just to what, capture him again?
-[Axatrax] Anyone see where my arm went? -And for the record, you didn't "save me."
translation.es: - ¿Alguien vio mi brazo? - Y conste que no me "salvaste".

translation.en: I was flying the hang glider.
translation.es: Yo volaba en un ala delta.

translation.en: Pageant prizes aren't always scholarships. Sometimes they're hang-gliding lessons.
translation.es: Los premios de belleza, a veces, son lecciones de ala delta.

translation.en: You were attached to me in the little BabyBjörn thing.
I was not a baby. My feet could touch. Green, about yea long.
translation.es: - No lo soy. Los pies me llegaban al piso. - Verde, así de largo…

translation.en: You may be good at throwing grenades, Matthew Mulligan,
but you are bad at president-ing, because you're selfish.
translation.es: pero eres mal presidente, porque eres egoísta.

translation.en: Oh yeah? Well, your dumb causes are dumb.
translation.es: ¿Ah, sí? Y tus tontas causas son tontas.

translation.en: Old people smell weird, fat kids are funny,
translation.es: Los ancianos huelen raro, los niños obesos dan risa,

translation.en: and animals are supposed to be food.
-We should be eating that thing. -[panda] Hmm?
translation.es: Deberíamos comernos eso que está ahí.

translation.en: Oh my God, you're the worst!
-Ugh! -No, wait, come back. I… I was just negging you, like in the book.
translation.es: Oye, regresa, me hacía el duro como dice ese libro para seducir.

translation.en: Lucy!
Oh, you love it.
She'll be here. Negging always works. Hey, no rush.
translation.es: - Vendrá. Hacerse el duro funciona. - No hay prisa.

translation.en: I'm just psyched to be doing priest stuff again.
translation.es: Me encanta volver a hacer de cura.

translation.en: Re-frocked, baby.
Uh, Mr. President, Lucy's not coming.
And if you ask me, this here's an opportunity.
translation.es: Para mí, esto es una oportunidad.

translation.en: Did you really wanna marry some chatty Catherine with a bunch of big ideas?
translation.es: ¿Quería casarse con una charlatana con ideas pretenciosas?

translation.en: But if she doesn't show up, it would be wicked embarrassing.
translation.es: Si no aparece, será un bochorno.

translation.en: Should I, like, pull a fire alarm or something?
Not hardly.
No, the people need their bread and circuses.
translation.es: El pueblo necesita pan y circo.

translation.en: Right, like a churro.
Oh, believe me, I've seen what happens when folks get disenchanted with a movement.
translation.es: Créame que sé lo que pasa cuando al pueblo algo lo defrauda.

translation.en: If we don't give 'em something they can believe in,
translation.es: Si no le damos algo en qué creer,

translation.en: those hippies out there are gonna turn into Charlie Mansonses,
translation.es: tendremos un ejército de Charles Mansons.

translation.en: which is why I arranged for backup.
-Wait, a what? -Sandra was an NFL cheerleader.
translation.es: - ¿Qué? - Sandra era porrista de la NFL.

translation.en: You know they're not allowed to wear underwear?
translation.es: ¿Sabía que no les permiten usar ropa interior?

translation.en: Wait, hold up. I feel like I should meet her first.
You and I, we're a team here, son.
I'm the brains and the fingers of America,
translation.es: Yo soy el cerebro y las manos del país.

translation.en: but you, you're its handsome face.
And for me to do my job,
all I need is for you to smile and give the people a little show.
translation.es: necesito que sonría y le dé a su pueblo un bonito show.

translation.en: Pretty as a painting, ain't she?
Now get it done!
So you have a ring, or do you need me to hook you up?
translation.es: ¿Tiene una sortija o le consigo una?

translation.en: I guess we're missing the president's wedding.
translation.es: Nos perdemos la boda del presidente.

translation.en: Screw him.
He's got to be the, like, fourth-worst president ever.
translation.es: Es el cuarto peor presidente de la historia.

translation.en: For reals! It's like the swamp is drained now.
'Cause the death rays boiled it.
Don't worry, we still got a couple of white guys in charge.
translation.es: Descuida, aún hay blancos al mando.

translation.en: Yeah! You know, before the aliens,
Senator LaMarr tried to make Black History Month
translation.es: LaMarr intentó hacer el Mes de la Historia Negra

translation.en: a one-day holiday on February 31st.
translation.es: en un feriado único el 31 de febrero.

translation.en: The president told me his favorite book is the script for Boondock Saints.
translation.es: El libro favorito del presidente es el guion de El quinto infierno.

translation.en: Yeah. [inhales]
Okay, so we should quit.
For sure. I mean, why bother trying to preserve a world
translation.es: Seguro. ¿Para qué intentar preservar un mundo que, por empezar, nadie valora?

translation.en: that no one ever appreciated to begin with?
translation.es: ¿Para qué intentar preservar un mundo que, por empezar, nadie valora?

translation.en: Seriously. The only thing anyone but us would miss in the whole Smithsonian
translation.es: Es cierto. Lo que todos menos nosotros extrañarían del Smithsoniano es la chaqueta de Fonzie.

translation.en: is, like, Fonzie's jacket.
translation.es: Lo que todos menos nosotros extrañarían del Smithsoniano es la chaqueta de Fonzie.

translation.en: Oh no, we can't lose Fonzie's jacket.
How will kids learn about Fonzies?
[TOD-209] TOD loot mimosas.
-[Dr. Braun] Whoo! -[Simon] Yeah!
Good luck without us, Mr. President.
Oh, this is full of broken glass. [TOD-209] TOD such a Miranda.
translation.es: - Tiene vidrios rotos. - TOD es una Miranda total.

translation.en: I couldn't go through with it, man.
Is this gonna be a regular thing now, or--
LaMarr wanted me to marry this cheerleader,
translation.es: LaMarr quería que me casara con la porrista,

translation.en: but I didn't even know her.
I mean, I don't know Lucy that good,
but she's brave, and she cares about stuff,
translation.es: pero es valiente, comprometida con sus causas

translation.en: and she's totally my type.
Yes, I remember your big speech.
And I am not on board with freckles, period.
translation.es: No estoy a favor de las pecas. Punto.

translation.en: I hooked up with this one chick whose face looked like--
translation.es: Una vez me acosté con una chica que parecía…

translation.en: LaMarr was pretty pissed.
He took a glove off a corpse and slapped me with it.
translation.es: Me abofeteó con un guante que le quitó a un muerto.

translation.en: But I don't know. I mean, I just couldn't get Lucy out of my head.
translation.es: No sé, no podía olvidar a Lucy.

translation.en: She hang glidered onto a spaceship,
translation.es: Planeó en ala delta hacia una nave

translation.en: and she said she believes in me.
translation.es: y dijo que creía en mí.

translation.en: No one's ever said that to me before.
I mean, my dad left his drywall business to my little sister.
translation.es: Mi papá le dejó su negocio a mi hermana menor.

translation.en: But I screwed it up with Lucy just like I screw up everything else.
translation.es: Pero la cagué con Lucy como con todo.

translation.en: -Honestly, Axie-- -Do not call me that.
translation.es: - En serio, Axie… - No me llames así.

translation.en: Part of me wishes you never even came to this planet.
translation.es: Ojalá no hubieras venido a este mundo.

translation.en: -Shazbot. -Why did you come here?
Earth is like a C-minus these days.
translation.es: La Tierra no es gran cosa últimamente.

translation.en: My planet is dying.
We used up all the natural resources on Cardi-B--
translation.es: Agotamos todos los recursos de Cardi-B.

translation.en: Your planet is named-- It's a coincidence!
translation.es: - ¿Tu planeta se llama…? - Es una casualidad.

translation.en: After we poisoned our environment,
my armada was sent to clear Earth for resettlement.
translation.es: enviaron a mi armada a despejar la Tierra para instalarnos.

translation.en: We were going to have a clean slate.
A chance to do it right this time.
translation.es: La oportunidad de hacer las cosas bien.

translation.en: Yes! That's it!
I'm a genius!
And I knew your arm would grow back! I don't believe you.
translation.es: - El brazo te volverá a crecer. - ¡No te creo!

translation.en: The measure passes. Gun ownership begins at conception.
translation.es: Moción aprobada. Se podrá portar armas desde la concepción.

translation.en: -[Matty] LaMarr! -Oh!
-Executive order! -[heroic music plays]
[TOD-209] Gang has several hours until curfew.
translation.es: Faltan algunas horas para el toque de queda.

translation.en: Checking movie listings.
The following movies are now playing:
No movies.
-Ugh, no kidding. -[woman] Hey.
You guys gotta get to the National Mall. Executive order.
translation.es: Hay que ir al National Mall. Decreto presidencial.

translation.en: Don't be scared, little animals. Oink, oink.
Roar!
Giraffe noise?
-Ah, Lucy. -Goshdamn it, Matty.
How'd you even find me here?
Two words. Helicopter.
Hi, Lucy. I helicoptered!
Hi, General Scarpaccio.
What do you want, Matty?
Come on, I gotta show you something.
Please? Ugh, fine.
Giraffe noise?
Wait, you did this?
[Matty] Yep. I executive ordered everyone to pour all the skunked beer on the museum fire.
translation.es: Sí, decreté que echaran su cerveza rancia sobre el fuego del museo.

translation.en: You know, to save all the crap.
-Huh. -I don't always just think of myself.
[Simon panting] Mr. President, this is amazing!
translation.es: No vivo pensando en mí. Sr. presidente, esto es increíble.

translation.en: Uh, ya think?
You see, I realized this whole mess could actually be a good thing.
translation.es: Creo que todo este desastre puede ser beneficioso.

translation.en: It's a clean slate. It's America 2: The Sequel!
translation.es: Es empezar de nuevo. Es EE. UU., Segunda Parte.

translation.en: Well, you're describing more of a reboot than a sequel, but… but sure.
translation.es: Es más una nueva versión que una segunda parte, pero sí.

translation.en: We rocked ass before.
Remember that fried chicken sandwich where the bread was fried chicken?
translation.es: ¿Recuerdan el sándwich de pollo frito con pollo frito como pan?

translation.en: But, okay, I'm gonna say it, America wasn't perfect.
translation.es: Pero, sí, debo admitir que el país no era perfecto.

translation.en: -What? Not America! -It isn't? Why wasn't I told?
'Cause some people couldn't get a fair shake,
no matter how many times he applied to The Bachelor. [sighs]
translation.es: por más veces que se hubieran anotado en The Bachelor.

translation.en: So let's make a new world.
One where a guy like me can win one for once.
translation.es: Uno donde alguien como yo gane algunas veces.

translation.en: Wow. Okay, maybe.
Also, maybe we could fulfill the promise of the Declaration of Independence.
translation.es: Y podríamos cumplir lo que dice la Declaración de la Independencia.

translation.en: And we can finally have equal pay and universal childcare.
translation.es: Y tener una paga equitativa y asistencia infantil universal.

translation.en: [TOD-209] Ha. Ha. Good one, Farrah.
Goddamn it. So yeah, let's save some stuff.
But only the good stuff.
I know how much you care about history.
translation.es: Sé que te importa mucho la historia.

translation.en: It's Fonzie's jacket.
Yes, history. Thank you, Mr. President.
What do you say? Can we start over?
Well, everyone deserves a second chance, even the whole world.
translation.es: Todos merecen una segunda oportunidad. Incluso el mundo entero.

translation.en: So, like, you and me have a real first date?
translation.es: ¿Quieres que tengamos una verdadera primera cita?

translation.en: I don't know if any Olive Gardens survived, but no Olive Garden, okay?
translation.es: No sé si el restaurante Olive Garden está en pie, pero ni se te ocurra.

translation.en: Let's all start over. Tabula rasa!
translation.es: Volvamos a empezar. Borrón y cuenta nueva.

translation.en: And let's get it right this time.
[TOD-209] Yes, it is a new--
[TOD-209 in distorted voice] Error. Replace brain tank fluid. Error.
-This guy. -TOD.
-Classic TOD. -Yeah, you said it.
Oh God, where are my kids?
That boy might could be a problem.
translation.es: Ese muchacho podría ser un problema.

translation.en: [Matty] Guys, I found a trumpet!
